main event: Two unidentified objects were observed over the Brunswick Naval Air Station in Maine on February 16, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were observed to hover, make quick starts, and hover again.
One of the objects appeared to be 30-40 feet long and had a grayish metal color.
The objects made a smooth, UFO-like passage sound and were estimated to be several hundred feet away.
One of the objects circled around a plane for a few minutes, moving quite fast at an estimated speed over 100 knots.
The observer had previously seen a similar bright, silvery-white object approach the land from the ocean in September 1965.
